# Fluff Date: 2026-02-13 13:54:40
overview:<p>The Titan II is a hundred-ton assault BattleMech produced by Kressly WarWorks on Epsilon Eridani for the Word of Blake's Protectorate Militia. First identified by the Successor States in 3071, the Titan II represents a more faithful modernization of the original Star League-era Titan prototype than the heavily modified Grand Titan that preceded it. Where Vining Engineering and Salvage Team had used the recovered Titan specifications as a jumping-off point for an entirely new design, Kressly's engineers hewed much closer to the original concept.</p><p>Although it shares a lineage with the Vining-designed Grand Titan, the Titan II is emphatically not that 'Mech. Built using standard construction technologies throughout (a standard engine, standard internal structure, and conventional armor) the Titan II eschews the weight-saving but fragile technologies favored by many modern designs. This approach reflects its intended role as a garrison 'Mech for the Protectorate Militia, where reliability and ease of production take precedence over cutting-edge performance.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Titan II retains the same Vlar 300 standard fusion engine and nineteen tons of Kressly Stoneskin 50 armor as its Star League-era ancestor, maintaining the original's philosophy of rugged survivability over speed. At fifty-four kilometers per hour, the Titan II relies on its heavy armor and firepower to dominate engagements rather than maneuver around opponents. The Kressly TIA-Infused chassis provides a solid foundation without resorting to expensive endo steel construction.</p><p>The weapons loadout modernizes the Titan concept with contemporary systems. A Blankenburg "Divine Wrath" Heavy PPC serves as the primary long-range weapon, backed by four Diplan M3-XR extended-range medium lasers that provide effective firepower at intermediate distances. A ZT Triple Fire Streak SRM-6 and twin Helga Series nine-tube multi-missile launchers handle close-range work, with the Streak system ensuring that every missile fired finds its target. Eighteen double heat sinks generally keep the Titan II operating within acceptable thermal limits. Notably absent from the design are the advanced C3 computer networks and other sophisticated electronics that characterize most Word of Blake military hardware, a deliberate omission that suggests the Protectorate is reserving its best technology for more elite formations.</p>

deployment:<p>The base TI-2P is the standard production model designed for Protectorate Militia garrison duty. Its combination of a Heavy PPC, extended-range medium lasers, multi-missile launchers, and a Streak SRM-6 provides effective firepower at all engagement ranges, while the heavily armored standard-engine design allows it to absorb significant punishment before being forced from the field. The deliberate exclusion of advanced electronics and weight-saving technologies keeps production costs manageable and simplifies maintenance for garrison technicians.</p>

history:<p>The Titan II's genesis lies in the Word of Blake's expansion of its Protectorate Militia during the early 3070s. As the Blakists consolidated control over their occupied worlds, they required large numbers of garrison 'Mechs that could be produced quickly and maintained by less experienced technicians. Kressly WarWorks on Epsilon Eridani, by then operating under Word of Blake authority, was directed to resurrect the original Titan specifications and produce an updated version suited to garrison duty.</p><p>The Titan II appeared on the battlefield in 3071, deployed primarily to Protectorate Militia forces garrisoning the worlds around Terra. While individual Titan IIs were occasionally spotted among Word of Blake Militia forces engaging coalition troops across the Inner Sphere, none were ever confirmed in service with the elite Manei Domini Shadow Divisions. This exclusion from the Word's most capable formations reinforced assessments that the Titan II was built for the Protectorate's second-line forces, with the Word's Precentor Martial restricting the best equipment for more devoted commands.</p><p>Following the fall of the Word of Blake, Kressly WarWorks continued production of the Titan II under new ownership. The factory on Epsilon Eridani transitioned through Republic of the Sphere control and continued manufacturing the design through the Dark Age, with the Titan II finding new buyers among the successor states that emerged from the Republic's fragmentation.</p>

